	   <tr><td colspan=2>I stand by adiemus that halfling druids are the way to go.&nbsp;&nbsp; I'm a halfling druid myself, and i love to see other halflings.  I even shout, on occasion Go 'lings!.<br><br>Thing about druids is that WIS is our primary stat, but we get the shaft on a lot of WIS items.  By level 50, it seems that it would be quite easy to get a cleric or a shammy to 200+wis, as the races that can play those classes (or at least some of them) have a natural wisdom of 100+.<br><br>The max druid WIS base is 90 (i think), so best to pump all the points you can into WIS.  After that, you got 5 left over.   I'd reccomend putting 'em in STR or AGI.  STR will help you carry more, and AGI will help out with the AC a little.  <br><br>I disagree with the CHA, as it seems to be easy to pump up.      My natural cha is 50, and for a small ammount of money (got it so long ago, i can't remember how much) but prolly less than 100pp (definatly less than 200pp), i was able to buy a charisma kit, and I'm able to pump CHA up to 105.  You can also get a buff from a high level enchanter/shaman.   I find that even with the low base CHA, i'm able to get rock bottom prices at merchants.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
