	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a note:&nbsp;&nbsp;I think several people are thinking of Ensnaring ROOT rather than the 29th level Ensnare (the upgrade to the Snare spell).  Ensnare does the same that Snare does, in that it slows down the mob, and doesn't break until the time runs out, or until some fool casts a ROOT on it that breaks in 10 seconds.   When kiting, I have found that Ensnare does last significantly longer than Snare.  Useful if you are using only DOTs to kite and medding while the mob catches up to you.  With the old one, I have to resnare every time my DOT wears off, and can be in trouble if it resists often.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
