	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 8:28 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.58]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't know how many of you use this tactic, saves alot of "Lost (insert spell here)" from your groupmates.<br><br>What I'll do is cast a buff on myself, then I'll buff each and every group member.&nbsp;&nbsp;What this does is let me know when buffs need to be refreshed.  My buff will start to go before any one else's, so as I refresh my buff, I also refresh the others in my group.  This way, I always know what buffs are up and when they need to be refreshed.<br><br>This is also usable on group buffs, you know when it's going so you can refresh without anyone having to ask for it.<br><br>Also, you should always announce a group buff before you cast to cause your group to get within range before casting.  <br><br>Oh well, just the ramblings of a level 51 druid, hope some of you find it useful.<br><br>Ashkevron Firstalker<br>Wanderer<br>Karana Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
