	   <tr><td colspan=2>While grouped I buff smart (in my oppinion).&nbsp;&nbsp;everyone gets a speed spell to evac if ness.  Only tanks get the armor and damage shield buff.  and usualy there is one player that always get hit so i give him the dammage shield only.  He usuly gets to pull if he hits the hardest and I wait in front of the group a little way to cast the dammage shield as soon as he is in range and before he has to stop.  This way I waist much less mana and time.  Too add further I ask what my job is from the group leader bafore we fight.  If there are any overlaping spells that are incompatiable we discouse this.  I was in a group once with 3 druids.  We split the root, dot, and heals and buffs up and we were the most efficient killing machine I to this day had a part in.<br><br><br>Not too exp, but learning quick.  Druid fo 20 seasons<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
