	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would say, that Evocation is the only specialization a druid needs. The skill is useful for using less mana and fewer fizzles, so it is best suited for combat spells. And the only ones which have to be delivered fast and hopefully cheap, are your DDs, which are all evocations, up to the 59th uber spell. <br><br>I grant, that Superior Heal also falls into this category, but it doesnt have that high a mana cost as many DDs, and it is only one spell.<br><br>For DoTs there is another reasoning...they are pretty mana efficient and you dont have to use that many on your victim(s), and it is usually no catastrophe, when you fizzle one (besides, a few of them are evocations...).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
