	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, when Kunark first came out, I found a glorious haven of experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Overthere had not been really explored at that time, and the most people I ever saw in zone was approx 5-7.  While exploring, I found an excellent place to hunt.  Travel across the zone until you reach the zone to the Skyfire Mountains.  If you camp right near that zone (outside the tunnel), and pull rhinos, Sarnaks, tigers, and cacti, you can get some FAST exp.  Best advice is to look for Kunark Rhinos and assorted Sabretooth Tigers/Tigeresses.  Cast Snare and then the highest animal fear you have.  From there, DoT as you choose (reverse-kiting, so your DoT will do full damage as long as the MoB is feared), and blast as you see fit.  This got me to 46-47 before the exp got too slow and boring.<br><br>My only warning is to ALWAYS check for Dragoons before pulling.  They can RIP you apart FAST, and be especially aware of Dragoon Barbers w'Selo.  He runs TOOOOOO fast.<br><br>Good travels, and good hunting!<br>&nbsp;<br>Aric Granath<br> - Yakage Tris'Adelfos, Druid, Tarew Marr</td></tr>
