	   <a name=966565870971></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f966565870971><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=966565870971>The soloing druid</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=966565870971#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 10:31 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi, I'll let you know now that i think druids are the best class in the game. I have attained the level 25 and I haven't been in group since lvl 16 or so. First off, there are two ways to solo. You can kite or root/dot, both methods work great. For kiting snare should be your first spell, then immediately throw your dot on. Run a bit then fire careless lighting twice. I tend to back-pedal so i can keep an eye on the mob. The reason to dot after you snare is this. When the dot wears off, you have about 30 seconds before snare goes too. It's mainly a warning signal for me. Repeat and you'll have yellows/reds down in 2-3 minutes. Ok, for the root technique. Obviously hit the mob with a root. Cast your dot and med. every 45 seconds or so re-apply the root and re-cast dot when it wears. Also when you hit 24 you can dot the use sunbeam. since they run away from you the dot does full damage! It's the same way witht he root. Hope this helps somebody. I went from 17-25 in a week and a half this way dying maybe 3 times. Good hunting friends. Drop me a tell if you have any questions.<br><br>Zaxnafein Dimeneira-Saryrn<br>Daoine the happy bard-Saryrn<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
