	   <tr><td colspan=2>I generally hunt in a group, but the easiest soloing for a druid is to fear kite.&nbsp;&nbsp;Find a griffawn or griffenne in North Karana, snare, DoT and then use terrorize animal.  You can sit and med while it runs slowly away, taking full damage from the DoT.  You even get messages now telling you when your spells wear off, providing an invaluable warning.<br><br>This tactic is much better after 24, though, as you can use creeping crud rather than stinging swarm, and lions won't aggro on you while you meditate in wolf form.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>tuttenclawstorm@yahoo.com<br></td></tr>
