	   <a name=96826591316251></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96826591316251><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96826591316251>Damage shields</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96826591316251#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=402><span id=Sage>Sage</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>18 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 6th 2:45 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Damage shields don't count towards damage dealt by the creature with the shield (or by the caster), and thus don't increase aggro chances.&nbsp;&nbsp;All this advice not to shield this or that class because of aggro problems isn't good advice.<br><br>Let's say you've got a mob on a single character with a damage shield.  If the character doesn't cause at least ten points of damage to the mob, it'll pop when it dies just as if killed by a NPC.  This is easy to verify for yourself with a low-level mob, and sometimes an unintentional consequence of a high-level damage shield on a low-level character who hasn't done enough damage to get credit for the kill.<br><br>Now, hopefully, a rogue won't be the primary target so they can do what they do best, but if the mobs do turn on them (and it's bound to happen after a particularly good backstab ;-), a damage shield won't make a bit of difference to how much he hates the rogue.  Conversely, it also won't help a tank taunt any better, either.<br><br>The choice of shielding monks and rogues should be solely based on whether they're often mob targets and worth the mana to shield.  Of course, if they firmly believe the shield increases aggro despite your assurances to the contrary, I'd humor them and not cast it on them.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
