	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 28th 2:16 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You are a master of versatility as a druid.&nbsp;&nbsp;So fill in the gaps and change your strategy depending on your party.  Thorn shields and dots are probably your best offense, but don't always make sense in some groups.  If mobs are going down too quickly, and pulls are too slow, then these dot spells including thorns are not mana efficient.  These things take time to be useful.  For example, in a caster heavy group taking on casting mobs, you're better off helping nuke to kill the darn things quickly. I also find it tough to thorn shield when you've got too many tanks and the mobs keep switching targets.  But thorns are awesome in two situations.  One is when you've got a controlled, drawn out fight where one or two ppl are taking all the hits.  Second is in a big ffa, like when attempting to break a spawn in a dungeon that you can't single pull.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
