	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I always cast damage shield on my tanks when group unless they are a monk or rogue :) It's an effective spell that helps guarentee the mob will stick on the tank and not the blasters if they do not over nuke.&nbsp;&nbsp;We were taking on red creatures with minimal deaths by having the attention of the mob stay where it should....on the tanks. The other spell that I throw on any mob right away is snare.  A runner can mean certain death in several situations.  Snare also means that the battle will only go until the creature begins the walk.  After that it becomes a beat on the monster until it's dead.  Mobs won't even defend themselves once they start the walk.  If they are rooted however, they will defend themselves.<br>&nbsp;<br>Milquetoast Outland<br>Druid of Tunare-Karana</td></tr>
